## 📏 CSS Units — What & Why

CSS units define how big or small elements and text appear on a webpage.

There are two main types of units:

- 🔴 Absolute units → fixed size  
- 🟢 Relative units → responsive (based on parent, root, or screen)

---

## 🔴 Absolute Units (Fixed)

These units **do not change** with screen size.

### ✅ px (most common)

```css
.box {
  width: 200px;
  font-size: 16px;
}
